{"art": [], "author": [{"email_address": "jgreenberg@politifact.com", "first_name": "Jon", "id": 257, "last_name": "Greenberg", "name_slug": "jon-greenberg", "on_staff_page": 5, "phone": "", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots16.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/257/", "title": "Staff Writer", "twitter": "JonZGreenberg"}], "canonical_url": "/punditfact/statements/2018/feb/16/usdeplorablesnewscom/fake-news-says-michelle-obama-blamed-donald-trump-/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Punditfact", "edition": "PunditFact", "edition_slug": "punditfact", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 48, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The PunditFact Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/48/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "asharockman@politifact.com", "first_name": "Aaron", "id": 114, "last_name": "Sharockman", "name_slug": "aaron-sharockman", "on_staff_page": 2, "phone": "727-553-4534", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots05.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/114/", "title": "Executive Director", "twitter": "asharock"}], "facebook_headline": "No, Michelle Obama did not blame Fla. shooting on Trump", "id": 15046, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "jgreenberg@politifact.com", "first_name": "Jon", "id": 257, "last_name": "Greenberg", "name_slug": "jon-greenberg", "on_staff_page": 5, "phone": "", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots16.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/257/", "title": "Staff Writer", "twitter": "JonZGreenberg"}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/15046/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "Pants on Fire", "id": 6, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/6/", "ruling": "Pants on Fire!", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-pantsonfire.gif", "ruling_slug": "pants-fire"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>Facebook users flagged a suspicious post on a site called <a href=\"http://usdeplorablesnews.com/index.php/2018/02/15/michelle-obama-florida-shooting-is-clearly-trumps-fault-these-shootings-are-happening-constantly-since-he-became-our-president-we-must-protect-our-children-from-this-tyrant/\">American President Donald J. Trump</a>. The headline read, &quot;Michelle Obama: &lsquo;Florida shooting is clearly Trump&rsquo;s fault, these shootings are happening constantly since he became our president.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The news brief said Obama made those comments &quot;in Chicago amid the Obama Foundation worldwide event.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But this story is a hoax.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.obama.org/updates/\">Obama Foundation</a> has not held an event since 19-year-old Nikolas Cruz killed 17 people at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Fla., on Feb. 14.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A search of the Nexis news database finds that former first lady Michelle Obama did not make those remarks at another event, or in any format whatsoever.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An identical article showed up on three websites &mdash;&nbsp;Usdeplorablesnews.com, <a href=\"http://usdeplorablesnews.com/index.php/2018/02/15/michelle-obama-florida-shooting-is-clearly-trumps-fault-these-shootings-are-happening-constantly-since-he-became-our-president-we-must-protect-our-children-from-this-tyrant/\">DailynewsforAmericans.com</a> and <a href=\"http://uberconservative.com/index.php/2018/02/15/michelle-obama-florida-shooting-clearly-trumps-happening/\">Uberconservative.com</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>None should be trusted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the aftermath of the Florida shooting, Michelle Obama retweeted the comments made by her husband, Barack Obama. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/BarackObama/status/964185606803853314\">He wrote</a>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are grieving with Parkland. But we are not powerless. Caring for our kids is our first job. And until we can honestly say that we&#39;re doing enough to keep them safe from harm, including long overdue, common-sense gun safety laws that most Americans want, then we have to change.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Websites claimed that Michelle Obama blamed Trump for the shooting in Florida. But she never said that. We rate this claim Pants on Fire.</p> <div class='artembed'>See Figure 1 on PolitiFact.com</div>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2018-02-16T14:45:23.057109", "ruling_date": "2018-02-16T14:52:53", "ruling_headline": "Fake news says Michelle Obama blamed Donald Trump for Florida shooting", "ruling_headline_slug": "fake-news-says-michelle-obama-blamed-donald-trump-", "ruling_link_text": "Fake, fake, fake", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>American President Donald J. Trump, <a href=\"http://usdeplorablesnews.com/index.php/2018/02/15/michelle-obama-florida-shooting-is-clearly-trumps-fault-these-shootings-are-happening-constantly-since-he-became-our-president-we-must-protect-our-children-from-this-tyrant/\">Michelle Obama: &lsquo;Florida Shooting Is Clearly Trump&rsquo;s Fault</a>, Feb. 15, 2018</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Obama Foundation, <a href=\"https://www.obama.org/updates/\">Updates</a>, accessed Feb. 16, 2018</p>\r\n", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 0, "current_job": "", "false_count": 0, "first_name": "usdeplorablesnews.com", "half_true_count": 0, "home_state": "", "id": 4208, "last_name": " ", "mostly_true_count": 0, "name_slug": "usdeplorablesnewscom", "pants_count": 1, "party": {"id": 3, "party": "Republican", "party_slug": "republican", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/party/3/"}, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/mugs/mug-bloggers.jpg", "primary_edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "National", "edition": "National", "edition_slug": "truth-o-meter", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 1, "index_page": true, "meter_name": "The Truth-O-Meter<sup>TM</sup>", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/1/"}, "promise_meter_cutout": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/person/4208/", "total_count": 1, "true_count": 0, "website": ""}, "statement": "<p>Says Michelle Obama said Florida shooting &quot;is clearly our president&rsquo;s fault.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n", "statement_context": "a fake news blog post", "statement_date": "2018-02-15", "statement_type": {"id": 2, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementtype/2/", "statement_type": "Claim", "type_description": "blog post "}, "subject": [{"description": "<p>There&rsquo;s an interesting discussion happening now about the spread of fake news on the Internet and what companies like Facebook, Google and Twitter, among others, should do to stop it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s a healthy conversation to have, and one we hope continues in the weeks and months ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But that doesn&rsquo;t mean we can&rsquo;t do something now. Here at PolitiFact, we&rsquo;re beefing up our coverage of fake news to help our readers better sort out fact from fiction on their social media feeds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claims can be about anything -- politics, entertainment, a fishy-sounding medical cure.</p>\r\n", "id": 323, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/subjects/mugs/fake.png", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/323/", "subject": "Fake news", "subject_slug": "fake-news", "used_in_edition": ["/api/v/2/edition/56/", "/api/v/2/edition/49/", "/api/v/2/edition/53/", "/api/v/2/edition/4/", "/api/v/2/edition/5/", "/api/v/2/edition/60/", "/api/v/2/edition/61/", "/api/v/2/edition/50/", "/api/v/2/edition/51/", "/api/v/2/edition/1/", "/api/v/2/edition/59/", "/api/v/2/edition/57/", "/api/v/2/edition/47/", "/api/v/2/edition/13/", "/api/v/2/edition/55/", "/api/v/2/edition/58/", "/api/v/2/edition/7/", "/api/v/2/edition/9/", "/api/v/2/edition/54/", "/api/v/2/edition/48/", "/api/v/2/edition/6/", "/api/v/2/edition/14/", "/api/v/2/edition/2/", "/api/v/2/edition/10/", "/api/v/2/edition/8/"]}, {"description": "", "id": 19, "photo": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/19/", "subject": "Guns", "subject_slug": "guns", "used_in_edition": ["/api/v/2/edition/1/"]}], "target": [], "twitter_headline": "Fake news: Michelle Obama blamed Fla. shooting on Trump"}